 who was related to me. He came over to Balla to ask about my mother, and asking after my mother's brother who was a vet and - but my mother's brother was dead and - and then he asked where my mother was. And they said, oh wel
l, she used to live in Ffestiniog but she's dead now. But I do remember they told him that she's got a son and he sometimes comes over to visit his uncle here. He's a naughty little devil too. And so this man said, oh well, I'd like to see him, because he
'
s a relative of mine and I've got the family history. And so he landed up here with a - a man from Balla But - I didn't happen to be in that day so he said he'd come over another time. And then he - and so he came over and he had the family tree with him,
 and he had it, he'd got it from Somerset House. And you see, I come from a - from a family of preachers, some of the best preachers in - in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Wales{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, the most famous. In fact they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16650296\charrsid11011264 three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid854880\charrsid11011264  preachers that started off the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16650296\charrsid11011264 Calvinistic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid854880\charrsid11011264  Methodist movement in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Wales{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. And there's the story of one of them preaching in Capelgwyn. He was William Evans from Vedw Arian. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16650296\charrsid11011264 
And it's so happened that I came into his will and I got a dresser and a few other things and there's a very interesting account of him preaching in Cape
lgwyn, and there's the story of him preaching in Hen Capel, you know, the one here, just - just in Ffestiniog. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid854880\charrsid11011264 
You know where it is? Who lives there now I wonder. You know, the road up to the quarry. You know, Manog quarry, the road up past Tryfal.
