\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6242166 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid854880\charrsid11011264 Do you remember if she worked after she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12287980 FE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid854880\charrsid11011264 Well I'll tell you what her father was, her father was a joiner, a tip-top joiner. And this is a
 very interesting story. When my uncle in Balla died he was a vet, he - he didn't own his house, he paid rent, and her - her father, joiner, had made a corner cupboard, which I've got in the house at the moment, this is in the kitchen. Now the things was,
 
my mother had a half sister and you see he, my uncle, made his will, and you see he promised a silver teapot to my mother's step-sister, half-sister And you see, she asked my uncle while he was very ill, on his deathbed, if she could take the silver teapo
t with her and he was pretty ill then. Of course, he said, And you know what this old bitch did? She packed three }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16650296\charrsid11011264 tea chests}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid854880\charrsid11011264 
 full of silver and stole them. Well now the old man was very ill and - an old couple, husband and wife came to live there to look af
ter him. And you see - the sister came to me and said that - that she had a copy of the will. And I said to her, I'm not interested in what's in the - what's in the will that you've got. She was the wife of a preacher. I'm going over there with a solicito
r
 to - to identify everything that's in the house to take an inventory in fact. Because you see, there's this couple living there and I've no idea what belongs to them and what belongs to my uncle, so I'm in charge now I said, I'm the executor of the will 
a
nd I'm taking the solicitor there with me, he was T.I. Jones. 'Cos I don't know, I mean, the people there might turn round and say, well this belongs to me, this belongs to me. And so I went. And - and he had to sign what my uncle had in the house, and th
e
 other party had to sign what they had. And then you see I had a call to say that my uncle was - very bad and I stayed there for a week. And this is a very funny story, I was there for a week and I could have stayed in a hotel over there but I didn't real
l
y have very much money. But they said, the couple, oh well, we can put you up. And so they did. And these people were very nice, everything for the best. And you see, when my uncle died, well my mother's step-sister and her husband didn't know that I was 
the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16650296\charrsid11011264 executor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid854880\charrsid11011264 
 of the will you see. And he came - came there with a solicitor. And I said to him, look here, this is the position. Oh, he said, we've got a list of everything that's in the house. And I said to him, I don't give a damn what you've got. I've go
t one here, dating from when I took charge of my uncle's affairs. Well, he said, my wife's got a list of - - which includes things like - blacking and boot polish. I don't give a damn what she's got, I said, this is the one that's going to stand, I said t
o
 him. The one I've got. And I said to him, by the way, I'd like your wife to bring back the blanket she pinched too. Oh I don't know anything about that, he said. Well she does, I said. You see these - these people here, this couple, were here when the so
licitor took identity of the charge. And she came over afterwards and pinched these blankets, two }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16650296\charrsid11011264 chestfuls}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid854880\charrsid11011264 
 and I'd like to get those back. And she had to send them back too. And the silver that - that she pinched, well - my uncle got that back before he di
ed in fact. That's very interesting, but this is the point now. But I said to them - the only thing that these people who've been staying here, who - who saved me from going to stay - stay in a hotel - the only thing they want is a - an old sewing machine
 
